HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 303
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Antonio "Tony" Santini of
Lawrenceburg.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Antonio "Tony" Santini; and
WHEREAS, Tony Santini was a highly respected member of his community and a
consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow
citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Santini was born on September 18, 1936, in Siderno Marina, Reggio
Calabria, Italy, but as his mother was unable to travel into town to register his birth until the next
day, his birthday was always celebrated on September 19; and
WHEREAS, growing up in Siderno, Tony Santini played soccer and fished in the lonian
Sea before joining the Italian Merchant Marines; through his service, he immigrated to the
United States, eventually settling in Massachusetts; and
WHEREAS, in Massachusetts, Mr. Santini met the love of his life, Lucille Medeiros
Santini, while working in a textile factory; the couple soon married and enjoyed sixty-one years
of marriage before his passing; and
WHEREAS, in 1964, the Santinis moved to Middle Tennessee, where Tony Santini had
received a promotion to manage factories; soon after the move, they started a family; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Santini's entrepreneurial spirit later led him to cattle farming and
establishing multiple successful businesses; and
WHEREAS, Tony Santini enjoyed fishing, spending time with his family and friends,
good Italian wine and food, and traveling to his hometown in Italy; his love for music often led
him to give impromptu concertos for his loved ones; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Santini was deeply devoted to his family and always endeavored to
remain true to family values of the highest order; and
