WHEREAS, in addition to his beloved wife, Tony Santini is survived by daughters, Maria
L. Santini and Annamaria Santini (Blake) Lay; sons, Frank Santini and Vince (Amy) Santini;
eight grandchildren, Alex Bolin, Britt Bolin, Francesca Lay, Aidan Lay, Sophia Santini, Kade Lay,
Nate Santini, and Crews Kroeger; as well as many nieces and nephews who cared deeply for
him; and
WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his mother, Maria Pellegrino Santini; father,
Ugo Santini; sisters, Giuseppina Sgambelluri and Angelina Barila; and brother, Francesco
"Frank" Santini; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Santini leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional gentleman; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Antonio "Tony" Santini, reflecting fondly upon his
impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and
conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Santini.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
